3:// Direct3d11_RenderTarget.cpp
4:// Phase 11 D3D11 renderer plugin -- offscreen baked-texture render
5:// target (RTV + paired SRV for sample-back).
6://
7:// Plan 11-04 (Wave 4 -- resource layer). Replaces createRenderTarget /
8:// setRenderTarget / copyRenderTargetToNonRenderTargetTexture scaffold
9:// stubs. Per CONTEXT D-13: no D3DPOOL_MANAGED / OnLostDevice /
10:// OnResetDevice -- D3D11 staging texture replaces D3D9's
11:// D3DPOOL_SYSTEMMEM bake surface. Per CONTEXT D-01: clean rewrite of the
12:// "render to baked texture, sample back" flow; Direct3d9_RenderTarget is
13:// design reference only.
14://
15:// The "primary" RTV/DSV is the back-buffer pair owned by
16:// Direct3d11_Device. setRenderTargetToPrimary just rebinds those via the
17:// device's beginScene helper. setRenderTarget(texture) routes draws to a
18:// secondary offscreen target backed by either a user-supplied Texture
19:// (already has its own ID3D11Texture2D+SRV via Direct3d11_TextureData) or
20:// the persistent 512x512 baked-texture pair created at install.
