codex
Bloom can still register on gl11 because its support gate is shader-capability based, even though 
gl11’s `setBloomEnabled` slot is deliberately a no-op. Its callback-owned textures are still 
ordinary D3D11 render-target `Texture` objects, so lost/restored is the resize mechanism for those 
allocations.
