One important non-callback state is not an extra texture: `Direct3d11_Device::ms_width/ms_height` 
feed the gl11 per-frame viewport. Any `resize(w,h)` implementation has to update those too, matching 
`displayModeChanged`; otherwise callbacks can resize PostFX while gl11’s own begin-scene viewport 
stays stale.
